to the editor mother superior guilty in rwanda killings news article june 9 noted that it was the first time a jury of ordinary citizens was asked to sit in judgment of war crimes in another nation this universal jurisdiction is the best way to ensure that the rwandan genocide does not go unpunished the belgian parliament integrated the united nations genocide convention and the geneva convention into belgian criminal law a step that could be taken in the united states and elsewhere in addition belgium and france have conducted painstaking parliamentary investigations into their roles in the genocide the two most prominent international players that have not assessed their involvement are the roman catholic church and the united states washington bears a major responsibility for pushing for the withdrawal of united nations forces which allowed the massacres to take place alain destexhe brussels june 14 2001 the writer is a member of the belgian senate

